---
import T7Layout from '../layouts/T7Layout.astro';
import MidPageCta from '../components/MidPageCta.astro';
import ContactForm from '../components/ContactForm.astro';
import { breadcrumbSchema } from '../lib/schema';

const title = 'Complaints Procedure';
const description =
  'How to raise a complaint with UK Mortgages Worldwide, what happens next, and how to refer a complaint to the Financial Ombudsman Service.';

const schemas = [
  breadcrumbSchema([
    { name: 'Home', path: '/' },
    { name: 'Complaints Procedure' },
  ]),
];
---

<T7Layout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  h1="Complaints Procedure"
  eyebrow="LEGAL"
  schemas={schemas}
>
  <p>
    UK Mortgages Worldwide takes complaints seriously. If something has
    gone wrong with the service we have provided, we want to know.
  </p>

  <h2>How to raise a complaint</h2>
  <p>You can raise a complaint with us by any of the following means:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Email: enquiry@ukmortgagesworldwide.com</li>
    <li>Post: Mortgage One, 555-557 Cranbrook Road, Gants Hill, Ilford, Essex, England IG2 6HE</li>
    <li>Phone: 01202 155992</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Please include your name, contact details, the nature of the
    complaint, and any relevant dates or reference numbers.
  </p>

  <h2>What happens next</h2>
  <p>
    We will acknowledge your complaint promptly, usually within 5 working
    days. We will then investigate and aim to provide a final response
    within 8 weeks. If our investigation takes longer than 8 weeks, we
    will write to you explaining the delay and setting out the next steps.
  </p>

  <h2>Financial Ombudsman Service</h2>
  <p>
    If you are not satisfied with our final response, or if 8 weeks have
    passed without a final response, you may refer your complaint to the
    Financial Ombudsman Service. The Financial Ombudsman Service is a
    free, independent service for resolving disputes between consumers
    and financial services firms.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Website: <a href="https://www.financial-ombudsman.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://www.financial-ombudsman.org.uk</a></li>
    <li>Phone: 0800 023 4567</li>
    <li>Address: Financial Ombudsman Service, Exchange Tower, London E14 9SR</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    You must usually refer a complaint to the Financial Ombudsman Service
    within six months of receiving our final response.
  </p>

  <h2>Financial Services Compensation Scheme</h2>
  <p>
    In the event that we are unable to meet our obligations, you may be
    entitled to compensation from the Financial Services Compensation
    Scheme. Mortgage advice and arrangement is covered up to 100% of the
    first £85,000 per eligible person, per firm. Insurance advice and
    arrangement is covered up to 100% of the claim with no upper limit.
    Eligibility criteria apply.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Website: <a href="https://www.fscs.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://www.fscs.org.uk</a></li>
  </ul>

  <MidPageCta variant="hero" />

  <ContactForm />
</T7Layout>
